WEBVTT

02:02.500 --> 02:04.834
- Obituaries.

02:04.900 --> 02:07.367
A man or a woman lives
their entire life.

02:07.433 --> 02:11.400
They work and love
and dream and laugh and cry,

02:11.467 --> 02:12.500
then they die.

02:16.233 --> 02:18.133
And then somebody
who they don't even know,

02:18.200 --> 02:21.100
who's never met them once,

02:21.166 --> 02:24.033
boils their entire life down
to a paragraph or two

02:24.100 --> 02:25.800
in a local newspaper,

02:25.867 --> 02:27.367
and that's only if
they've achieved something,

02:27.433 --> 02:30.300
something that the editor
thinks is important.

02:30.367 --> 02:32.600
Now, if they're real movers,
real shakers,

02:32.667 --> 02:34.700
maybe they get two columns,

02:34.767 --> 02:38.000
maybe they get a photo
from 1974.

02:40.233 --> 02:43.266
And if they've achieved nothing,

02:43.333 --> 02:45.533
they get buried
at the bottom of the page,

02:45.600 --> 02:47.333
or ignored completely.

02:55.133 --> 02:58.000
- The homicide unit
has finished its investigation.

02:58.066 --> 02:59.767
Guillaume Tarrant
shot seven people

02:59.834 --> 03:02.000
before killing himself.

03:02.066 --> 03:04.400
Four people are dead:
Officer Joseph Howard,

03:04.467 --> 03:06.400
and prisoners Lou Rath,
Junior Pierce,

03:06.467 --> 03:08.100
and Kenny Wangler.
- What's the status

03:08.166 --> 03:10.533
of the other three inmates,
Keller, Cyran, and Ahmed?

03:10.600 --> 03:12.033
- They're all
at Benchley Memorial.

03:12.100 --> 03:14.800
Cyran and Ahmed
had superficial wounds.

03:14.867 --> 03:18.600
They should be back today,
but, Keller had internal damage.

03:18.667 --> 03:20.867
He'll be in the hospital awhile.

03:20.934 --> 03:22.500
You know,
I keep asking myself:

03:22.567 --> 03:25.300
How did that fucking gun
get in Oz?

03:25.367 --> 03:26.467
- I don't know, Murphy,

03:26.533 --> 03:29.400
but, I'm sure as Christ
gonna find out.

03:29.467 --> 03:31.767
- We don't know
where the gun came from.

03:31.834 --> 03:33.467
- Why you asking us?

03:33.533 --> 03:35.734
That was a white man's finger
on the trigger.

03:35.800 --> 03:37.700
- I'm talking to everyone.

03:37.767 --> 03:40.800
- Whether you find out
the truth or not,

03:40.867 --> 03:43.000
one thing is clear.

03:43.066 --> 03:45.166
Emerald City is out of control.

03:45.233 --> 03:47.734
McManus must go.

03:47.800 --> 03:50.934
- You telling me who to hire
and who to fire, Adebisi?

03:51.000 --> 03:52.700
- Just pointing out reality.

03:52.767 --> 03:54.567
- McManus was lax.

03:54.633 --> 03:57.200
Ultimately,
the responsibility is his.

03:57.266 --> 03:59.500
And you'd better act fast,
the press wants answers.

03:59.567 --> 04:01.333
Public wants someone to blame.

04:01.400 --> 04:04.900
- Thank you for your concern.

04:04.967 --> 04:07.633
- You two were very chummy
in there.

04:07.700 --> 04:10.633
Rare finding such agreement.

04:10.700 --> 04:14.033
- So, you are saying you don't
want McManus to get fired?

04:16.233 --> 04:19.133
- Zahir, what is going on?

04:19.200 --> 04:21.033
- What do you care?

04:21.100 --> 04:23.133
You lost the taste for power,
isn't that what you said?

04:23.200 --> 04:25.400
- Yeah.
- Then you're out of this.

04:25.467 --> 04:26.834
- Beginning of the day,

04:26.900 --> 04:29.433
the way, the wisdom,
the wish, the will to treat,

04:29.500 --> 04:31.166
to try, to trip.
- Shut up.

04:31.233 --> 04:32.600
- You can memorialize
them hacks...

04:32.667 --> 04:34.233
- Shut the fuck up already!
- But, my brothers,

04:34.300 --> 04:36.000
they on they backs
in corners like--

04:36.066 --> 04:38.734
like roaches after another
fucking raid sweepin'.

04:38.800 --> 04:40.133
- Enough!
Shut the fuck up, man!

04:40.200 --> 04:41.700
- Back on the thigh,
the glimmer in the eye.

04:43.200 --> 04:44.467
- Poet.

04:44.533 --> 04:47.100
Poet, enough.
- Stupid ass motherfucker.

04:47.166 --> 04:48.667
- Get the fuck away from me,
man.

04:48.734 --> 04:51.100
You know, Bricks--
Bricks and Junior is dead.

04:51.166 --> 04:53.967
They dead!
- You and me are alive.

04:54.033 --> 04:55.834
- Ain't got no heart, Adebisi.

04:55.900 --> 04:57.533
- I have a heart.

04:57.600 --> 04:59.667
I have a heart of a lion.

04:59.734 --> 05:02.600
Instead of crying
for Kenny and Junior,

05:02.667 --> 05:05.233
help me revenge them.

05:05.300 --> 05:07.100
- Revenge against who, Adebisi?

05:07.166 --> 05:10.834
You seen Tarrant
greased himself.

05:10.900 --> 05:13.934
- You see,
against them.

05:14.000 --> 05:16.967
All of those white bastards.

05:17.033 --> 05:19.033
- Wasn't no fucking
white bastard,

05:19.100 --> 05:20.533
that poured hot soup
on my face,

05:20.600 --> 05:21.800
scarring my skin.

05:21.867 --> 05:23.633
That was you.
That was you!

05:23.700 --> 05:26.266
- Yeah, that was then.
This is now.

05:26.333 --> 05:28.166
If you'd been standing
1 inch to the left

05:28.233 --> 05:29.767
when the shooting started,
you'd be dead

05:29.834 --> 05:33.867
and Kenny Wangler would be
my new best friend.

05:38.333 --> 05:40.567
- Yo, brother,
shit's going down.

05:40.633 --> 05:41.967
- Yeah, but, what?

05:42.033 --> 05:44.133
We're on the outside,
nose against the glass.

05:44.200 --> 05:46.266
- Yeah, not for long, brother.

05:46.333 --> 05:49.100
Fucking hacks want to know
how Frenchy got the gun.

05:49.166 --> 05:51.166
- And you know who did it?

05:51.233 --> 05:53.800
- Fucking coco, man.
Adebisi.

05:53.867 --> 05:56.367
I saw him with the gun
the day before the shooting.

05:56.433 --> 05:58.300
- Does Adebisi know you know?

05:58.367 --> 05:59.433
- Not yet, brah,

05:59.500 --> 06:03.000
but he gonna find out
soon enough.

06:07.033 --> 06:08.333
- Integrity.

06:08.400 --> 06:10.600
It's what sets
real leaders apart

06:10.667 --> 06:12.633
from typical politicians.

06:12.700 --> 06:16.166
One man running for governor
has real integrity.

06:16.233 --> 06:17.333
Alvah Case.

06:17.400 --> 06:20.100
Activist lawyer,
law school dean,

06:20.166 --> 06:22.100
State Bar president.

06:22.166 --> 06:24.767
Nobody questions his integrity.

06:24.834 --> 06:27.533
So, after the riots
at Oswald Prison,

06:27.600 --> 06:30.533
to whom did even James Devlin
turn to sort it out?

06:30.600 --> 06:31.800
That's right...

06:37.333 --> 06:39.367
- Wendy.

06:40.767 --> 06:42.567
- McManus has to go.

06:42.633 --> 06:44.033
- That seems to be
the mantra of the week.

06:44.100 --> 06:45.700
- Have you seen The Trib?

06:45.767 --> 06:47.567
Front page,
above the fold.

06:47.633 --> 06:49.967
"Prison Shooting
Leaves Four Dead."

06:50.033 --> 06:51.533
And two op-ed pieces.

06:51.600 --> 06:53.700
- I can handle
a little negative press.

06:53.767 --> 06:56.100
- Not if you want
to be lieutenant governor.

06:56.166 --> 06:59.266
You need a scapegoat.
You have to fire McManus.

06:59.333 --> 07:01.200
- Now's not the time.

07:01.266 --> 07:02.934
- He screwed things up
from the get-go.

07:03.000 --> 07:06.233
Have you forgotten the riot?
- The riot was not Tim's fault.

07:06.300 --> 07:09.166
- His entire history of Emerald
City has been a disaster.

07:09.233 --> 07:11.367
He's a weak,
limp-wristed liberal

07:11.433 --> 07:13.767
and you gotta toss him out
with the other garbage.

07:21.533 --> 07:23.567
- Here's your mail.

07:25.200 --> 07:26.734
You're welcome.

07:48.600 --> 07:50.500
- "Dear Tim,
I know by now

07:50.567 --> 07:52.266
that Sister Pete
has given you the news

07:52.333 --> 07:54.200
"that I'm not coming back to Oz.

07:54.266 --> 07:56.400
"This all must seem
unreal to you.

07:56.467 --> 07:58.600
"It sure as hell does to me.

07:58.667 --> 08:00.500
"When I left two weeks ago
on vacation,

08:00.567 --> 08:02.166
"I never dreamed my entire life

08:02.233 --> 08:05.000
"could turn around
so far so fast.

08:05.066 --> 08:07.767
"I never dreamed that
I'd meet a man like Cary.

08:07.834 --> 08:10.600
So loving,
so understanding..."

08:41.467 --> 08:44.000
- I've been asked
to pick one staff member

08:44.066 --> 08:46.867
to serve as part of
a state delegation

08:46.934 --> 08:48.600
that's going to South Africa

08:48.667 --> 08:51.800
for a discussion
of human rights issues.

08:51.867 --> 08:54.533
That group will visit
the Pretoria Prison,

08:54.600 --> 08:58.500
the Zonder Water Prison,
as well as go on a safari.

08:58.567 --> 09:00.200
- Sorry.

09:00.266 --> 09:02.500
Uh, Leo, I just want to talk
for one minute, okay?

09:02.567 --> 09:03.700
- Not now.
I'm in the middle of something.

09:03.767 --> 09:04.934
- Ah, yeah,
just one minute

09:05.000 --> 09:07.100
about Officer Howard's
memorial service.

09:07.166 --> 09:08.667
You know,
it's important, goddamn it,

09:08.734 --> 09:12.100
because the man was killed
right in front of me.

09:13.467 --> 09:15.500
- All right, go ahead.

09:17.533 --> 09:19.233
Okay, uh...

09:19.300 --> 09:21.500
I think that
we should videotape the ceremony

09:21.567 --> 09:25.433
so that when his grandkids
get older they can watch it.

09:26.867 --> 09:30.133
- Eternal rest grant unto him,
oh, Lord,

09:30.200 --> 09:33.200
and let perpetual light
shine down upon him.

09:33.266 --> 09:35.300
all: Amen.

09:35.367 --> 09:37.967
- And now, Tim McManus would
like to say a few words.

09:38.033 --> 09:40.200
Tim.

09:41.100 --> 09:45.867
- Uh,
Joe loved to bet on the horses,

09:45.934 --> 09:49.333
and so, in honor of him,
I would like to...

