♪ Camp town ladies
sing this song ♪

09:52.700 --> 09:55.700
♪ Doo-da, doo-da ♪

09:55.767 --> 09:59.166
♪ Camp town racetrack's
five miles long ♪

09:59.233 --> 10:02.100
♪ Oh, doo-da-day ♪

10:02.166 --> 10:05.166
♪ Gonna run all night ♪

10:05.233 --> 10:07.800
♪ Gonna run all day ♪

10:07.867 --> 10:10.967
♪ Bet my money
on a bob-tail nag ♪

10:11.033 --> 10:13.633
♪ Somebody bet on the bay ♪

10:15.100 --> 10:17.800
- Come in.

10:17.867 --> 10:21.000
- Leo, we want
to talk about Tim.

10:21.066 --> 10:23.033
I have had all the discussions

10:23.100 --> 10:24.367
about Tim McManus
I'm gonna have.

10:24.433 --> 10:26.300
- He's clearly in distress.

10:26.367 --> 10:27.767
- Yes.
- He needs help.

10:27.834 --> 10:29.867
- That's what I told him.
- So, you've seen him?

10:29.934 --> 10:32.266
- We've been looking everywhere.
- He just left.

10:32.333 --> 10:33.400
- Well, where'd he go?

10:33.467 --> 10:34.934
- I have no idea.

10:35.000 --> 10:36.500
- All right,
we'll try him at home tonight.

10:36.567 --> 10:38.266
- If not, we'll just
see him here tomorrow.

10:38.333 --> 10:39.700
- Right.
- I don't think so.

10:39.767 --> 10:40.900
- Why not?

10:40.967 --> 10:42.633
- I just fired him.

10:42.700 --> 10:44.800
Goodnight.

10:48.433 --> 10:51.200
- I saw this obituary once
of a guy I knew,

10:51.266 --> 10:55.166
and the newspaper
had misspelled his name.

10:55.233 --> 10:59.367
They misspelled his goddamn,
motherfucking name,

10:59.433 --> 11:01.734
and that's it.
It ain't no going back.

11:01.800 --> 11:03.333
It's not like they
gonna get his name right

11:03.400 --> 11:05.066
the next time he dies.

11:05.133 --> 11:07.734
No.
That edition of the newspaper

11:07.800 --> 11:10.734
is going in the archives.

11:12.600 --> 11:14.133
And this guy I know,
his name,

11:14.200 --> 11:17.266
which is probably the thing
he's proudest of in life,

11:17.333 --> 11:19.667
it's gonna be wrong

11:19.734 --> 11:22.500
forever and ever.

11:44.834 --> 11:46.633
- All right.

11:46.700 --> 11:49.133
Everybody, listen up.

11:49.200 --> 11:50.700
Last night,

11:50.767 --> 11:53.800
Tim McManus resigned
as unit manager of Emerald City.

11:58.000 --> 11:59.667
- All right, quiet down.

11:59.734 --> 12:02.000
Until a new unit manager
is named,

12:02.066 --> 12:04.467
the warden has asked me
to temporarily

12:04.533 --> 12:06.667
take over McManus' duties.

12:06.734 --> 12:08.066
Hear this.

12:08.133 --> 12:09.266
Nothing,

12:09.333 --> 12:11.300
and I mean nothing's
gonna change.

12:11.367 --> 12:14.233
- Yeah, that's what you think.
- Alright, that's it.

12:17.700 --> 12:19.266
- Officer Murphy,

12:19.333 --> 12:21.000
have you heard the latest
on Chris Keller?

12:21.066 --> 12:23.533
- Haven't heard anything new.

12:23.600 --> 12:26.133
- Could you call 'em
and check on his status?

12:26.200 --> 12:27.900
- Beecher, we had
a major incident here,

12:27.967 --> 12:29.834
all right?
Now, we lose Tim McManus.

12:29.900 --> 12:34.133
Your boyfriend's health
ain't a priority for me.

12:34.200 --> 12:35.667
- Please?

12:35.734 --> 12:37.367
- Go away.

12:40.066 --> 12:42.967
- I asked my father to locate
Schillinger's other son.

12:43.033 --> 12:46.300
- Oz didn't make you a bitch.

12:46.367 --> 12:48.100
You were born one.

12:48.166 --> 12:50.667
- Yeah, okay.
- Yeah.

12:53.367 --> 12:54.967
- You were tormented
in your role in the death

12:55.033 --> 12:56.500
over Andrew ScHillinger.

12:56.567 --> 12:58.233
You went looking,
you came to me.

12:58.300 --> 13:00.900
You asked for guidance
in the ways of Islam.

13:00.967 --> 13:02.934
You felt comfort,

13:03.000 --> 13:05.600
peace of mind
in the arms of Allah.

13:05.667 --> 13:07.500
But, you have this

13:07.567 --> 13:09.333
thing

13:09.400 --> 13:11.533
between you and Keller.

13:11.600 --> 13:14.166
Homosexual acts are blasphemy.

13:16.300 --> 13:18.600
I know that.

13:18.667 --> 13:21.266
I don't want to love him,
Kareem,

13:21.333 --> 13:23.367
but, I do.

13:23.433 --> 13:24.834
And as for Allah,

13:24.900 --> 13:27.166
I'll take my chances with him
when the time comes.

13:32.700 --> 13:34.166
- Hey, Beecher.

13:34.233 --> 13:36.600
Sorry about what happened
to your little butt buddy.

13:36.667 --> 13:38.767
Of course, knowing that kind,

13:38.834 --> 13:40.166
he's probably fucked
half his nurses

13:40.233 --> 13:43.433
and a couple orderlies by now.

13:43.500 --> 13:44.500
Hope he don't come back to you

13:44.567 --> 13:46.266
with any of them
staph infections.

13:58.100 --> 14:00.100
- Toby.
Hey, Dad.

14:00.166 --> 14:02.533
- Oh.

14:02.600 --> 14:04.300
Good news.

14:04.367 --> 14:08.333
We found Hank ScHillinger,
by the way.

14:08.400 --> 14:10.200
- Well, Jesus, that was fast.

14:10.266 --> 14:12.467
- Well, I told you,
Swannie's the best,

14:12.533 --> 14:14.333
and if you turn
over the right rock,

14:14.400 --> 14:16.500
you'll find a worm.

14:16.567 --> 14:18.533
- Meaning?

14:18.600 --> 14:21.100
- Hank Schillinger's
one screwed up kid.

14:21.166 --> 14:23.400
Swannie said he's a--
he's a drug addict,

14:23.467 --> 14:25.300
he's a petty thief.

14:25.367 --> 14:28.900
He pimped his girlfriend.

14:28.967 --> 14:31.400
- How long before he'll come
and visit ScHillinger?

14:31.467 --> 14:33.667
- Well, there's one
slight complication.

14:33.734 --> 14:37.066
Boy says he won't come
unless he gets paid.

14:37.133 --> 14:38.233
- Paid.
How much?

14:38.300 --> 14:39.633
- I don't know.

14:39.700 --> 14:42.967
Probably what it'll cost
to get him his next high.

14:43.033 --> 14:45.967
Mm.

14:46.033 --> 14:48.133
Make the deal.

14:48.200 --> 14:50.967
- Toby.
- Make the deal, Dad.

14:59.066 --> 15:01.266
- Vern.

15:01.333 --> 15:04.700
- What the hell--sorry,
heck do you want?

15:04.767 --> 15:06.166
- You have a visitor.

15:06.233 --> 15:09.934
- What, suddenly you're
my appointment secretary?

15:10.000 --> 15:11.767
- Hank is here.

15:11.834 --> 15:13.367
- Hank?

15:13.433 --> 15:15.767
My hank?

15:29.400 --> 15:32.667
- Your father's on his way.

15:32.734 --> 15:35.734
- So, when do I get
the other half of the money?

15:35.800 --> 15:38.166
- When you're done.

15:38.233 --> 15:39.667
- Cool.

15:39.734 --> 15:41.834
So, bring him on.

15:45.567 --> 15:47.367
How long is this gonna take?

15:47.433 --> 15:50.100
'cause I gotta meet somebody.

15:54.100 --> 15:57.900
Dude, you look awesome.

15:57.967 --> 16:00.033
- Hello, son.

16:00.100 --> 16:02.200
- Skinny as shit.

16:02.266 --> 16:03.367
They don't feed you in here?

16:03.433 --> 16:05.233
- Oh.

16:05.300 --> 16:08.600
Oh, God!
Good to see you.

16:08.667 --> 16:10.400
- Dad.

16:10.467 --> 16:12.166
- Let me look at you.

16:13.233 --> 16:15.934
- Yeah.

16:16.000 --> 16:17.700
- How you doing?

16:17.767 --> 16:20.800
I mean, about Andrew.

16:20.867 --> 16:23.600
- Well, I miss him,

16:23.667 --> 16:25.533
but, before he got clipped,

16:25.600 --> 16:28.133
we weren't hanging
as much together.

16:28.200 --> 16:30.000
All the freaks he'd be with,

16:30.066 --> 16:32.100
dragging a nigger
from the back of a truck.

16:32.166 --> 16:34.767
What is that shit?

16:35.900 --> 16:37.133
- Well, go on, sit down.

16:37.200 --> 16:39.066
So much I want
to talk to you about.

16:39.133 --> 16:40.600
- You know,
I'd love that,

16:40.667 --> 16:42.834
but, I mean,
I gotta bolt.

16:44.333 --> 16:47.266
- Hank, you just got here.

16:47.333 --> 16:49.133
Hank.

16:49.200 --> 16:52.200
- You know, fuck it.

16:52.266 --> 16:53.667
I got time.

16:53.734 --> 16:57.100
I mean, you're my daddy, right?

17:05.533 --> 17:06.800
- How'd it go?

17:06.867 --> 17:08.734
- Well, it started out
kind of bizarre,

17:08.800 --> 17:11.533
but, Hank eventually
settled down.

17:11.600 --> 17:13.400
- And ScHillinger?

17:13.467 --> 17:14.600
- You know, I've actually
never seen him happy,

17:14.667 --> 17:18.033
but, that's what he seems to be.

17:18.100 --> 17:20.300
He asked Hank to come back,
Hank said yes,

17:20.367 --> 17:23.000
but, whether he shows up
is anybody's guess.

17:23.066 --> 17:25.100
- I'll make sure he does.

17:25.166 --> 17:27.767
- You know,
the most startling thing for me

17:27.834 --> 17:31.200
is how much ScHillinger
truly loves this kid.

17:32.300 --> 17:34.266
- Father?
- Yeah?

17:34.333 --> 17:37.400
- Have you ever loved
anybody too much?

17:39.000 --> 17:41.934
Of course, you're not allowed.

17:42.000 --> 17:44.400
I mean, the celibacy thing.

17:44.467 --> 17:46.233
I guess my question is:

17:46.300 --> 17:48.066
Is it wrong

17:48.133 --> 17:51.467
to love somebody too much?

17:51.533 --> 17:55.200
- Well, I guess that depends on
how the love manifests itself.

17:57.400 --> 18:01.367
And the answer
to your first question is...

18:01.433 --> 18:03.233
yes, I have.

18:07.867 --> 18:09.200
- You gotta pity the guy

18:09.266 --> 18:11.867
who had one thing go
wrong in his whole life.

18:11.934 --> 18:15.400
I mean, other than that
one thing that got fucked up,

18:15.467 --> 18:17.467
he led a good,
average life.

18:17.533 --> 18:19.367
But, some incident or other,

18:19.433 --> 18:22.266
some bad decision
or bad behavior

